758
00:32:36,832 --> 00:32:38,290
You'll see everything
is in effect,

759
00:32:38,290 --> 00:32:39,610
an action, and a resource.

760
00:32:39,610 --> 00:32:42,065
The effect is either
allow or deny.

761
00:32:42,065 --> 00:32:43,190
Do I allow this permission?

762
00:32:43,190 --> 00:32:44,380
Do I explicitly deny it?

763
00:32:44,380 --> 00:32:47,160
Explicit allow, explicit deny.

764
00:32:47,160 --> 00:32:50,910
The action specifies
the API calls that can

765
00:32:50,910 --> 00:32:52,810
be made against an AWS service.

766
00:32:52,810 --> 00:32:55,000
If you guys aren't familiar
with APIs, it's OK.

767
00:32:55,000 --> 00:32:56,860
It's application
programming interface.

768
00:32:56,860 --> 00:32:59,460
This is what we're talking
about, that programmatic access.

769
00:32:59,460 --> 00:33:01,860
