00:33:09,040 --> 00:33:15,120
That's a call I'm making, a
request I'm making to AWS,

774
00:33:15,120 --> 00:33:17,940
and then it's returning me
some sort of information.

775
00:33:17,940 --> 00:33:20,708
And so the action specifies the
API calls that are allowed here.

776
00:33:20,708 --> 00:33:22,500
So you see all of these
different ones that

777
00:33:22,500 --> 00:33:26,820
are explicitly allowed are
API calls that they can do.

